32// The maximum expected growth from adding a VUI to the SPS. It's actually
33// closer to 24 or so, but better safe than sorry.
34const size_t kMaxVuiSpsIncrease = 64;
35
36const char* kSpsValidHistogramName = "WebRTC.Video.H264.SpsValid";
37enum SpsValidEvent {
38 kReceivedSpsVuiOk = 1,
39 kReceivedSpsRewritten = 2,
40 kReceivedSpsParseFailure = 3,
41 kSentSpsPocOk = 4,
42 kSentSpsVuiOk = 5,
43 kSentSpsRewritten = 6,
44 kSentSpsParseFailure = 7,
45 kSpsRewrittenMax = 8
46};
47
48#define RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(x) \
49 do { \
50 if (!(x)) { \
51 RTC_LOG_F(LS_ERROR) << " (line:" << __LINE__ << ") FAILED: " #x; \
52 return false; \
53 } \
54 } while (0)
55
56#define COPY_UINT8(src, dest, tmp) \
57 do { \
58 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL((src)->ReadUInt8(tmp)); \
59 if (dest) \
60 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL((dest)->WriteUInt8(tmp)); \
61 } while (0)
62
63#define COPY_EXP_GOLOMB(src, dest, tmp) \
64 do { \
65 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL((src)->ReadExponentialGolomb(tmp)); \
66 if (dest) \
67 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL((dest)->WriteExponentialGolomb(tmp)); \
68 } while (0)
69
70#define COPY_BITS(src, dest, tmp, bits) \
71 do { \
72 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL((src)->ReadBits(bits, tmp)); \
73 if (dest) \
74 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL((dest)->WriteBits(tmp, bits)); \
75 } while (0)
76

78 rtc::BitBuffer* source,
79 rtc::BitBufferWriter* destination,
80 const webrtc::ColorSpace* color_space,
81 SpsVuiRewriter::ParseResult* out_vui_rewritten);

83 rtc::BitBufferWriter* destination);

85 uint32_t max_num_ref_frames);

88 const ColorSpace& color_space);

90 rtc::BitBuffer* source,
91 rtc::BitBufferWriter* destination,

93 SpsVuiRewriter::ParseResult* out_vui_rewritten);
94bool CopyRemainingBits(rtc::BitBuffer* source,
95 rtc::BitBufferWriter* destination);
96} // namespace

98void SpsVuiRewriter::UpdateStats(ParseResult result, Direction direction) {
99 switch (result) {
100 case SpsVuiRewriter::ParseResult::kVuiRewritten:
101 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION(
102 kSpsValidHistogramName,
103 direction == SpsVuiRewriter::Direction::kIncoming
104 ? SpsValidEvent::kReceivedSpsRewritten
105 : SpsValidEvent::kSentSpsRewritten,
106 SpsValidEvent::kSpsRewrittenMax);
107 break;
108 case SpsVuiRewriter::ParseResult::kVuiOk:
109 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION(
110 kSpsValidHistogramName,
111 direction == SpsVuiRewriter::Direction::kIncoming
112 ? SpsValidEvent::kReceivedSpsVuiOk
113 : SpsValidEvent::kSentSpsVuiOk,
114 SpsValidEvent::kSpsRewrittenMax);
115 break;
116 case SpsVuiRewriter::ParseResult::kFailure:
117 RTC_HISTOGRAM_ENUMERATION(
118 kSpsValidHistogramName,
119 direction == SpsVuiRewriter::Direction::kIncoming
120 ? SpsValidEvent::kReceivedSpsParseFailure
121 : SpsValidEvent::kSentSpsParseFailure,
122 SpsValidEvent::kSpsRewrittenMax);
123 break;
124 }
125}
126
127SpsVuiRewriter::ParseResult SpsVuiRewriter::ParseAndRewriteSps(
128 const uint8_t* buffer,
129 size_t length,
130 absl::optional<SpsParser::SpsState>* sps,
131 const webrtc::ColorSpace* color_space,
132 rtc::Buffer* destination) {
133 // Create temporary RBSP decoded buffer of the payload (exlcuding the
134 // leading nalu type header byte (the SpsParser uses only the payload).
135 std::vector<uint8_t> rbsp_buffer = H264::ParseRbsp(buffer, length);
136 rtc::BitBuffer source_buffer(rbsp_buffer.data(), rbsp_buffer.size());
137 absl::optional<SpsParser::SpsState> sps_state =
138 SpsParser::ParseSpsUpToVui(&source_buffer);
139 if (!sps_state)
140 return ParseResult::kFailure;
141
142 *sps = sps_state;
143
144 // We're going to completely muck up alignment, so we need a BitBuffer to
145 // write with.
146 rtc::Buffer out_buffer(length + kMaxVuiSpsIncrease);
147 rtc::BitBufferWriter sps_writer(out_buffer.data(), out_buffer.size());
148
149 // Check how far the SpsParser has read, and copy that data in bulk.
150 size_t byte_offset;
151 size_t bit_offset;
152 source_buffer.GetCurrentOffset(&byte_offset, &bit_offset);
153 memcpy(out_buffer.data(), rbsp_buffer.data(),
154 byte_offset + (bit_offset > 0 ? 1 : 0)); // OK to copy the last bits.
155
156 // SpsParser will have read the vui_params_present flag, which we want to
157 // modify, so back off a bit;
158 if (bit_offset == 0) {
159 --byte_offset;
160 bit_offset = 7;
161 } else {
162 --bit_offset;
163 }
164 sps_writer.Seek(byte_offset, bit_offset);
165
166 ParseResult vui_updated;
167 if (!CopyAndRewriteVui(*sps_state, &source_buffer, &sps_writer, color_space,
168 &vui_updated)) {
169 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to parse/copy SPS VUI.";
170 return ParseResult::kFailure;
171 }
172
173 if (vui_updated == ParseResult::kVuiOk) {
174 // No update necessary after all, just return.
175 return vui_updated;
176 }
177
178 if (!CopyRemainingBits(&source_buffer, &sps_writer)) {
179 RTC_LOG(LS_ERROR) << "Failed to parse/copy SPS VUI.";
180 return ParseResult::kFailure;
181 }
182
183 // Pad up to next byte with zero bits.
184 sps_writer.GetCurrentOffset(&byte_offset, &bit_offset);
185 if (bit_offset > 0) {
186 sps_writer.WriteBits(0, 8 - bit_offset);
187 ++byte_offset;
188 bit_offset = 0;
189 }
190
191 RTC_DCHECK(byte_offset <= length + kMaxVuiSpsIncrease);
192 RTC_CHECK(destination != nullptr);
193
194 out_buffer.SetSize(byte_offset);
195
196 // Write updates SPS to destination with added RBSP
197 H264::WriteRbsp(out_buffer.data(), out_buffer.size(), destination);
198
199 return ParseResult::kVuiRewritten;
200}
201
202SpsVuiRewriter::ParseResult SpsVuiRewriter::ParseAndRewriteSps(
203 const uint8_t* buffer,
204 size_t length,
205 absl::optional<SpsParser::SpsState>* sps,
206 const webrtc::ColorSpace* color_space,
207 rtc::Buffer* destination,
208 Direction direction) {
209 ParseResult result =
210 ParseAndRewriteSps(buffer, length, sps, color_space, destination);
211 UpdateStats(result, direction);
212 return result;
213}
214
215rtc::Buffer SpsVuiRewriter::ParseOutgoingBitstreamAndRewrite(
216 rtc::ArrayView<const uint8_t> buffer,
217 const webrtc::ColorSpace* color_space) {
218 std::vector<H264::NaluIndex> nalus =
219 H264::FindNaluIndices(buffer.data(), buffer.size());
220
221 // Allocate some extra space for potentially adding a missing VUI.
222 rtc::Buffer output_buffer(/*size=*/0, /*capacity=*/buffer.size() +
223 nalus.size() * kMaxVuiSpsIncrease);
224
225 for (const H264::NaluIndex& nalu : nalus) {
226 // Copy NAL unit start code.
227 const uint8_t* start_code_ptr = buffer.data() + nalu.start_offset;
228 const size_t start_code_length =
229 nalu.payload_start_offset - nalu.start_offset;
230 const uint8_t* nalu_ptr = buffer.data() + nalu.payload_start_offset;
231 const size_t nalu_length = nalu.payload_size;
232
233 if (H264::ParseNaluType(nalu_ptr[0]) == H264::NaluType::kSps) {
234 // Check if stream uses picture order count type 0, and if so rewrite it
235 // to enable faster decoding. Streams in that format incur additional
236 // delay because it allows decode order to differ from render order.
237 // The mechanism used is to rewrite (edit or add) the SPS's VUI to contain
238 // restrictions on the maximum number of reordered pictures. This reduces
239 // latency significantly, though it still adds about a frame of latency to
240 // decoding.
241 // Note that we do this rewriting both here (send side, in order to
242 // protect legacy receive clients) in RtpDepacketizerH264::ParseSingleNalu
243 // (receive side, in orderer to protect us from unknown or legacy send
244 // clients).
245 absl::optional<SpsParser::SpsState> sps;
246 rtc::Buffer output_nalu;
247
248 // Add the type header to the output buffer first, so that the rewriter
249 // can append modified payload on top of that.
250 output_nalu.AppendData(nalu_ptr[0]);
251
252 ParseResult result = ParseAndRewriteSps(
253 nalu_ptr + H264::kNaluTypeSize, nalu_length - H264::kNaluTypeSize,
254 &sps, color_space, &output_nalu, Direction::kOutgoing);
255 if (result == ParseResult::kVuiRewritten) {
256 output_buffer.AppendData(start_code_ptr, start_code_length);
257 output_buffer.AppendData(output_nalu.data(), output_nalu.size());
258 continue;
259 }
260 } else if (H264::ParseNaluType(nalu_ptr[0]) == H264::NaluType::kAud) {
261 // Skip the access unit delimiter copy.
262 continue;
263 }
264
265 // vui wasn't rewritten and it is not aud, copy the nal unit as is.
266 output_buffer.AppendData(start_code_ptr, start_code_length);
267 output_buffer.AppendData(nalu_ptr, nalu_length);
268 }
269 return output_buffer;
270}

272namespace {
273bool CopyAndRewriteVui(const SpsParser::SpsState& sps,
274 rtc::BitBuffer* source,
275 rtc::BitBufferWriter* destination,
276 const webrtc::ColorSpace* color_space,
277 SpsVuiRewriter::ParseResult* out_vui_rewritten) {
278 uint32_t golomb_tmp;
279 uint32_t bits_tmp;
280
281 *out_vui_rewritten = SpsVuiRewriter::ParseResult::kVuiOk;
282
283 //
284 // vui_parameters_present_flag: u(1)
285 //
286 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteBits(1, 1));
287
288 // ********* IMPORTANT! **********
289 // Now we're at the VUI, so we want to (1) add it if it isn't present, and
290 // (2) rewrite frame reordering values so no reordering is allowed.
291 if (!sps.vui_params_present) {
292 // Write a simple VUI with the parameters we want and 0 for all other flags.
293
294 // aspect_ratio_info_present_flag, overscan_info_present_flag. Both u(1).
295 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteBits(0, 2));
296
297 uint32_t video_signal_type_present_flag =
298 (color_space && !IsDefaultColorSpace(*color_space)) ? 1 : 0;
299 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(
300 destination->WriteBits(video_signal_type_present_flag, 1));
301 if (video_signal_type_present_flag) {
302 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(AddVideoSignalTypeInfo(destination, *color_space));
303 }
304 // chroma_loc_info_present_flag, timing_info_present_flag,
305 // nal_hrd_parameters_present_flag, vcl_hrd_parameters_present_flag,
306 // pic_struct_present_flag, All u(1)
307 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteBits(0, 5));
308 // bitstream_restriction_flag: u(1)
309 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteBits(1, 1));
310 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(
311 AddBitstreamRestriction(destination, sps.max_num_ref_frames));
312
313 *out_vui_rewritten = SpsVuiRewriter::ParseResult::kVuiRewritten;
314 } else {
315 // Parse out the full VUI.
316 // aspect_ratio_info_present_flag: u(1)
317 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 1);
318 if (bits_tmp == 1) {
319 // aspect_ratio_idc: u(8)
320 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 8);
321 if (bits_tmp == 255u) { // Extended_SAR
322 // sar_width/sar_height: u(16) each.
323 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 32);
324 }
325 }
326 // overscan_info_present_flag: u(1)
327 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 1);
328 if (bits_tmp == 1) {
329 // overscan_appropriate_flag: u(1)
330 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 1);
331 }
332
333 CopyOrRewriteVideoSignalTypeInfo(source, destination, color_space,
334 out_vui_rewritten);
335
336 // chroma_loc_info_present_flag: u(1)
337 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 1);
338 if (bits_tmp == 1) {
339 // chroma_sample_loc_type_(top|bottom)_field: ue(v) each.
340 COPY_EXP_GOLOMB(source, destination, golomb_tmp);
341 COPY_EXP_GOLOMB(source, destination, golomb_tmp);
342 }
343 // timing_info_present_flag: u(1)
344 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 1);
345 if (bits_tmp == 1) {
346 // num_units_in_tick, time_scale: u(32) each
347 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 32);
348 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 32);
349 // fixed_frame_rate_flag: u(1)
350 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 1);
351 }
352 // nal_hrd_parameters_present_flag: u(1)
353 uint32_t nal_hrd_parameters_present_flag;
354 COPY_BITS(source, destination, nal_hrd_parameters_present_flag, 1);
355 if (nal_hrd_parameters_present_flag == 1) {
356 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(CopyHrdParameters(source, destination));
357 }
358 // vcl_hrd_parameters_present_flag: u(1)
359 uint32_t vcl_hrd_parameters_present_flag;
360 COPY_BITS(source, destination, vcl_hrd_parameters_present_flag, 1);
361 if (vcl_hrd_parameters_present_flag == 1) {
362 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(CopyHrdParameters(source, destination));
363 }
364 if (nal_hrd_parameters_present_flag == 1 ||
365 vcl_hrd_parameters_present_flag == 1) {
366 // low_delay_hrd_flag: u(1)
367 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 1);
368 }
369 // pic_struct_present_flag: u(1)
370 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 1);
371
372 // bitstream_restriction_flag: u(1)
373 uint32_t bitstream_restriction_flag;
374 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(source->ReadBits(1, bitstream_restriction_flag));
375 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteBits(1, 1));
376 if (bitstream_restriction_flag == 0) {
377 // We're adding one from scratch.
378 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(
379 AddBitstreamRestriction(destination, sps.max_num_ref_frames));
380 *out_vui_rewritten = SpsVuiRewriter::ParseResult::kVuiRewritten;
381 } else {
382 // We're replacing.
383 // motion_vectors_over_pic_boundaries_flag: u(1)
384 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 1);
385 // max_bytes_per_pic_denom: ue(v)
386 COPY_EXP_GOLOMB(source, destination, golomb_tmp);
387 // max_bits_per_mb_denom: ue(v)
388 COPY_EXP_GOLOMB(source, destination, golomb_tmp);
389 // log2_max_mv_length_horizontal: ue(v)
390 COPY_EXP_GOLOMB(source, destination, golomb_tmp);
391 // log2_max_mv_length_vertical: ue(v)
392 COPY_EXP_GOLOMB(source, destination, golomb_tmp);
393 // ********* IMPORTANT! **********
394 // The next two are the ones we need to set to low numbers:
395 // max_num_reorder_frames: ue(v)
396 // max_dec_frame_buffering: ue(v)
397 // However, if they are already set to no greater than the numbers we
398 // want, then we don't need to be rewriting.
399 uint32_t max_num_reorder_frames, max_dec_frame_buffering;
400 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(
401 source->ReadExponentialGolomb(max_num_reorder_frames));
402 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(
403 source->ReadExponentialGolomb(max_dec_frame_buffering));
404 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteExponentialGolomb(0));
405 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(
406 destination->WriteExponentialGolomb(sps.max_num_ref_frames));
407 if (max_num_reorder_frames != 0 ||
408 max_dec_frame_buffering > sps.max_num_ref_frames) {
409 *out_vui_rewritten = SpsVuiRewriter::ParseResult::kVuiRewritten;
410 }
411 }
412 }
413 return true;
414}
415
416// Copies a VUI HRD parameters segment.
417bool CopyHrdParameters(rtc::BitBuffer* source,
418 rtc::BitBufferWriter* destination) {
419 uint32_t golomb_tmp;
420 uint32_t bits_tmp;
421
422 // cbp_cnt_minus1: ue(v)
423 uint32_t cbp_cnt_minus1;
424 COPY_EXP_GOLOMB(source, destination, cbp_cnt_minus1);
425 // bit_rate_scale and cbp_size_scale: u(4) each
426 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 8);
427 for (size_t i = 0; i <= cbp_cnt_minus1; ++i) {
428 // bit_rate_value_minus1 and cbp_size_value_minus1: ue(v) each
429 COPY_EXP_GOLOMB(source, destination, golomb_tmp);
430 COPY_EXP_GOLOMB(source, destination, golomb_tmp);
431 // cbr_flag: u(1)
432 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 1);
433 }
434 // initial_cbp_removal_delay_length_minus1: u(5)
435 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 5);
436 // cbp_removal_delay_length_minus1: u(5)
437 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 5);
438 // dbp_output_delay_length_minus1: u(5)
439 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 5);
440 // time_offset_length: u(5)
441 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, 5);
442 return true;
443}
444
445// These functions are similar to webrtc::H264SpsParser::Parse, and based on the
446// same version of the H.264 standard. You can find it here:
447// http://www.itu.int/rec/T-REC-H.264
448
449// Adds a bitstream restriction VUI segment.
450bool AddBitstreamRestriction(rtc::BitBufferWriter* destination,
451 uint32_t max_num_ref_frames) {
452 // motion_vectors_over_pic_boundaries_flag: u(1)
453 // Default is 1 when not present.
454 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteBits(1, 1));
455 // max_bytes_per_pic_denom: ue(v)
456 // Default is 2 when not present.
457 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteExponentialGolomb(2));
458 // max_bits_per_mb_denom: ue(v)
459 // Default is 1 when not present.
460 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteExponentialGolomb(1));
461 // log2_max_mv_length_horizontal: ue(v)
462 // log2_max_mv_length_vertical: ue(v)
463 // Both default to 16 when not present.
464 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteExponentialGolomb(16));
465 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteExponentialGolomb(16));
466
467 // ********* IMPORTANT! **********
468 // max_num_reorder_frames: ue(v)
469 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteExponentialGolomb(0));
470 // max_dec_frame_buffering: ue(v)
471 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteExponentialGolomb(max_num_ref_frames));
472 return true;
473}
474
475bool IsDefaultColorSpace(const ColorSpace& color_space) {
476 return color_space.range() != ColorSpace::RangeID::kFull &&
477 color_space.primaries() == ColorSpace::PrimaryID::kUnspecified &&
478 color_space.transfer() == ColorSpace::TransferID::kUnspecified &&
479 color_space.matrix() == ColorSpace::MatrixID::kUnspecified;
480}
481
482bool AddVideoSignalTypeInfo(rtc::BitBufferWriter* destination,
483 const ColorSpace& color_space) {
484 // video_format: u(3).
485 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteBits(5, 3)); // 5 = Unspecified
486 // video_full_range_flag: u(1)
487 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteBits(
488 color_space.range() == ColorSpace::RangeID::kFull ? 1 : 0, 1));
489 // colour_description_present_flag: u(1)
490 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteBits(1, 1));
491 // colour_primaries: u(8)
492 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(
493 destination->WriteUInt8(static_cast<uint8_t>(color_space.primaries())));
494 // transfer_characteristics: u(8)
495 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(
496 destination->WriteUInt8(static_cast<uint8_t>(color_space.transfer())));
497 // matrix_coefficients: u(8)
498 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(
499 destination->WriteUInt8(static_cast<uint8_t>(color_space.matrix())));
500 return true;
501}
502
503bool CopyOrRewriteVideoSignalTypeInfo(
504 rtc::BitBuffer* source,
505 rtc::BitBufferWriter* destination,
506 const ColorSpace* color_space,
507 SpsVuiRewriter::ParseResult* out_vui_rewritten) {
508 // Read.
509 uint32_t video_signal_type_present_flag;
510 uint32_t video_format = 5; // H264 default: unspecified
511 uint32_t video_full_range_flag = 0; // H264 default: limited
512 uint32_t colour_description_present_flag = 0;
513 uint8_t colour_primaries = 3; // H264 default: unspecified
514 uint8_t transfer_characteristics = 3; // H264 default: unspecified
515 uint8_t matrix_coefficients = 3; // H264 default: unspecified
516 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(source->ReadBits(1, video_signal_type_present_flag));
517 if (video_signal_type_present_flag) {
518 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(source->ReadBits(3, video_format));
519 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(source->ReadBits(1, video_full_range_flag));
520 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(source->ReadBits(1, colour_description_present_flag));
521 if (colour_description_present_flag) {
522 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(source->ReadUInt8(colour_primaries));
523 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(source->ReadUInt8(transfer_characteristics));
524 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(source->ReadUInt8(matrix_coefficients));
525 }
526 }
527
528 // Update.
529 uint32_t video_signal_type_present_flag_override =
530 video_signal_type_present_flag;
531 uint32_t video_format_override = video_format;
532 uint32_t video_full_range_flag_override = video_full_range_flag;
533 uint32_t colour_description_present_flag_override =
534 colour_description_present_flag;
535 uint8_t colour_primaries_override = colour_primaries;
536 uint8_t transfer_characteristics_override = transfer_characteristics;
537 uint8_t matrix_coefficients_override = matrix_coefficients;
538 if (color_space) {
539 if (IsDefaultColorSpace(*color_space)) {
540 video_signal_type_present_flag_override = 0;
541 } else {
542 video_signal_type_present_flag_override = 1;
543 video_format_override = 5; // unspecified
544
545 if (color_space->range() == ColorSpace::RangeID::kFull) {
546 video_full_range_flag_override = 1;
547 } else {
548 // ColorSpace::RangeID::kInvalid and kDerived are treated as limited.
549 video_full_range_flag_override = 0;
550 }
551
552 colour_description_present_flag_override =
553 color_space->primaries() != ColorSpace::PrimaryID::kUnspecified ||
554 color_space->transfer() != ColorSpace::TransferID::kUnspecified ||
555 color_space->matrix() != ColorSpace::MatrixID::kUnspecified;
556 colour_primaries_override =
557 static_cast<uint8_t>(color_space->primaries());
558 transfer_characteristics_override =
559 static_cast<uint8_t>(color_space->transfer());
560 matrix_coefficients_override =
561 static_cast<uint8_t>(color_space->matrix());
562 }
563 }
564
565 // Write.
566 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(
567 destination->WriteBits(video_signal_type_present_flag_override, 1));
568 if (video_signal_type_present_flag_override) {
569 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteBits(video_format_override, 3));
570 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(
571 destination->WriteBits(video_full_range_flag_override, 1));
572 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(
573 destination->WriteBits(colour_description_present_flag_override, 1));
574 if (colour_description_present_flag_override) {
575 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(destination->WriteUInt8(colour_primaries_override));
576 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(
577 destination->WriteUInt8(transfer_characteristics_override));
578 RETURN_FALSE_ON_FAIL(
579 destination->WriteUInt8(matrix_coefficients_override));
580 }
581 }
582
583 if (video_signal_type_present_flag_override !=
584 video_signal_type_present_flag ||
585 video_format_override != video_format ||
586 video_full_range_flag_override != video_full_range_flag ||
587 colour_description_present_flag_override !=
588 colour_description_present_flag ||
589 colour_primaries_override != colour_primaries ||
590 transfer_characteristics_override != transfer_characteristics ||
591 matrix_coefficients_override != matrix_coefficients) {
592 *out_vui_rewritten = SpsVuiRewriter::ParseResult::kVuiRewritten;
593 }
594
595 return true;
596}
597
598bool CopyRemainingBits(rtc::BitBuffer* source,
599 rtc::BitBufferWriter* destination) {
600 uint32_t bits_tmp;
601 // Try to get at least the destination aligned.
602 if (source->RemainingBitCount() > 0 && source->RemainingBitCount() % 8 != 0) {
603 size_t misaligned_bits = source->RemainingBitCount() % 8;
604 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, misaligned_bits);
605 }
606 while (source->RemainingBitCount() > 0) {
607 auto count = rtc::SafeMin<size_t>(32u, source->RemainingBitCount());
608 COPY_BITS(source, destination, bits_tmp, count);
609 }
610 // TODO(noahric): The last byte could be all zeroes now, which we should just
611 // strip.
612 return true;
613}
